> This French-inspired favorite combines the best of breakfast into one creamy, dreamy sandwich. Crusty sourdough, creamy mustard sauce, savory prosciutto, and melty gouda are topped with a fried egg and grated Parmesan, then finished with chives for a pop of freshness. Accompanied by a light, citrusy salad starring pickled shallot, this sumptuous meal is fit for a queen.

Adjust oven rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Peel and thinly slice @shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered). Finely chop @chives{1/4%oz}(finely chopped).

== Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @cream sauce base{4%oz} and half @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}. Season with @pepper{}.

== Sandwiches ==

Arrange half the @sourdough bread{2%slices} on one side of a #baking sheet{}. Spread with a thin layer of mustard cream sauce, then top with @prosciutto{2%oz}, @gouda cheese{2%slices}, and another drizzle of mustard cream sauce. Arrange remaining @sourdough bread{2%slices} on empty side of sheet; spread with a thin layer of mustard cream sauce.

Bake on middle rack until bread is golden, cheese begins to melt, and prosciutto is lightly browned, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use two baking sheets; bake bread with prosciutto and gouda on top rack and bread with sauce on middle rack.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. (TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.) Once hot, crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. Fry eggs until whites are set, ~{1-2%minutes} (they'll finish cooking later). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Pickled Shallot Salad ==

While eggs cook, in a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine shallot, juice from two lemon wedges, @sugar{1%tsp}, @water{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use juice from four lemon wedges, 2 tsp sugar, and 2 tsp water.

Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{1%minute}. Reserve 2 TBSP pickling liquid (4 TBSP for 4), then drain.

In a third small bowl, whisk together reserved pickling liquid, remaining @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, and @olive oil{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

== Assembly ==

Once bread has toasted 6-8 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully top bread with prosciutto and gouda with toasted bread, sauce sides down, to create sandwiches. Top with half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tbsp}, fried eggs, and a drizzle of remaining mustard cream sauce. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.

Heat broiler to high. Return to oven until cheese melts and eggs are cooked to preference, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Salad ==

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%oz} and pickled shallot with dressing.

== To Serve ==

Divide sandwiches between plates. Garnish with chives. Serve salad and remaining lemon wedges on the side.